The problem MSPEC involves finding a cut in an edge-weighted graph, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also has applications in wireless sensor networks, which suggests a possible category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of "powers" at vertices and the objective of minimizing their sum suggests a possible category of information theory (cs.IT). The problem also involves finding a measure of barrier coverage, which suggests a possible category of computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper mentions the problem's relationship to network flow and matching problems, which suggests a possible category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
